> This Peri Peri Spiced Chorizo Pilaf combines the Indian technique of pilaf, a
> sautéed rice dish, with Portuguese flavours. Peri peri contains smoked paprika,
> ancho chilli powder, ground cumin and oregano.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting lid) on
medium heat.

Once hot, add half the @butter{1%tbsp} and allow to melt. Add the
@diced British chicken breast{240%g} and onion, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden and softened,
~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.
Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Once the onions have softened, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until it
starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Next, add the garlic, @Peri Peri seasoning{2%sachets} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}, stir-fry
for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Stir in the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and allow it to evaporate, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @basmati rice{150%g} into the pan until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @water{300%ml} and @chicken stock paste{15%g}. Bring to the
boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, quarter the @lemon{1}(quartered).

Once ready, stir the @peas{120%g}, @red pepper chilli jelly{25%g} and a good
squeeze of lemon juice into the rice along with the remaining @butter{1%tbsp}.

Pop the lid back on and allow to stand for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and lemon juice if you feel it needs it. Add
a splash of @water{} if it's a little dry.

Share the peri peri spiced chicken and chorizo pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Finish with a drizzle of @soured cream{75%g} and any remaining lemon wedges
alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!